OL,3,CWorld's oldest wine discovered in
OL,4,CSpain contains human bones,
OL,5,Cresearchers say
OL,7,FA team from the Department of Organic
OL,8,FChemistry were initially unsure if the
OL,9,Fred-tinged substance was wine, and it
OL,10,Fhad lost many of its characteristic
OL,11,Fcomponents after being sealed in the
OL,12,Ftomb since the first century AD.
OL,14,FAfter studying its pH and chemical
OL,15,Fcompounds present in the substance,
OL,16,Fresearchers were able to identify the
OL,17,Fsubstance by finding polyphenols -
OL,18,Fbiomarkers present in wine.
