OL,3,CWorld's oldest wine discovered in
OL,4,CSpain contains human bones,
OL,5,Cresearchers say
OL,7,FThe find has replaced the Speyer wine
OL,8,Fbottle, which was discovered in a
OL,9,FRoman tomb in Germany in 1867. Up
OL,10,Funtil now, it was considered be the
OL,11,Fworld's oldest wine, dating back to
OL,12,Fbetween 325 and 350 AD.
OL,14,FResearchers still cannot pinpoint the
OL,15,Fwine's origin, but they found seven
OL,16,Fspecific polyphenols that were also
OL,17,Fpresent in wines from Montilla-
OL,18,FMoriles, Jerez or Sanlucar.
