OL,3,CWorld's oldest wine discovered in
OL,4,CSpain contains human bones,
OL,5,Cresearchers say
OL,7,FRoman tombs often contained
OL,8,Fpossessions the dead to accompany them
OL,9,Fin their journey to the afterlife.
OL,11,FAccording to the research team, the
OL,12,Ffact the bones submerged in the wine
OL,13,Fbelonged to a man was no surprise, as
OL,14,Fwomen were forbidden from drinking in
OL,15,Fancient Rome.
OL,17,FThe University of Cordoba said the
OL,18,Fdiscovery shed "a lot of light on the
OL,19,Ffunerary rituals of ancient Rome" and
OL,20,Foffered a chance for the deceased
OL,21,Fcompanions to be "remembered again".
